# WPF GUI coding rules

## Named controls

Every control that PowerShell needs to touch must have `x:Name="..."` in XAML.
Retrieve via `function Find($name) { $window.FindName($name) }`.

## Updating UI from background code

Use `$control.Dispatcher.Invoke({ ... })` if you're on a non-UI thread. Timers
(`DispatcherTimer`) run on the UI thread by default — safe to update controls directly.

## Styling

- Dark theme colors defined in `<Window.Resources>` as `Color` + `SolidColorBrush` pairs.
- Never hardcode colors in controls — use `{StaticResource AccentBrush}` etc.
- Card style: `Style="{StaticResource Card}"` — don't duplicate the rounded-rect + shadow pattern.
- Buttons: `PrimaryBtn` (accent fill) or `GhostBtn` (surface + border). `IconBtn` for chevron/toggles.

## Scrolling

- Main `ScrollViewer` has `x:Name="mainScroll"` and `CanContentScroll="False"` so pixel-based scrolling works with our smooth-scroll easing (22% per 14ms tick).
- Don't set fixed heights on body content — let the scroll handle overflow.

## Icon drawing

The app icon is generated via `New-AppIcon` using `DrawingVisual` + `RenderTargetBitmap`:
- background: rounded rect with 3-stop linear gradient (header colors)
- glow: radial gradient ellipse
- lightning bolt: `Geometry.Parse("M 74,18 ... Z")` in 128-space, scaled via `PushTransform`
- "8": `FormattedText` in Segoe UI Black, drawn AFTER the bolt so it sits on top

Coordinates are in 128-unit space; everything scales by `$size / 128`.

## Stepper state machine

`Set-Step $dot $icon $sub $num $state $subText` where `$state ∈ { pending, active, done }`.

- `pending`: muted bg, shows the digit
- `active`: accent bg + glow effect, shows the digit (never stale)
- `done`: green bg, shows `[char]0x2713` (✓) — Unicode, not Segoe MDL2 glyph

Always pass `$num` so text doesn't get stuck on a previous glyph.

## Avoid

- `Get-Content -Raw` for XAML → use `[IO.File]::ReadAllText(..., [Text.Encoding]::UTF8)`.
- `$geom.Transform = ...` on a parsed Geometry (it's frozen) → use `DrawingContext.PushTransform`.
- Mixing FontFamily with glyph codepoint — Segoe MDL2 glyphs won't render in Segoe UI.
